author: Mark Hiner
message: Add test for same type varargs/single-var conflict

author: Mark Hiner
message:
Resolve ambiguity of same varargs/single-var type

Fixes an ambiguity when we have overloaded method signatures, where one
method is a varargs of a type identical the single-variable parameter of
another method, for example: m1="method(double...)" and
m2="method(double)". In this case we now say m2 is more specific than
m1.

author: Karl Nelson
message:
Merge pull request #878 from hinerm/convert_booleans

Add booleans to primitive convert list

author: Mark Hiner
message:
MethodResolution: enable boolean resolution

Adds the Java primitive class, Boolean.TYPE, to the conversion map in
MethodResolution. This allows equivalent boolean parameters in overloaded
methods to be appropriately considered assignable to each other.

Prior to this patch, overloaded methods "m1(boolean, Object...)" and
"m1(boolean, Map)" would be treated as unresolvable due to the perceived
inequality of boolean parameters.

* Specialize NotRunning

message:
Merge pull request #332 from vstinner/patch-1

Fix #331: Don't call Py_Initialize() in PyInit__jpype() to support Python 3.7

author: Victor Stinner
message:
Fix #331: Don't call Py_Initialize() in PyInit__jpype() to support Python 3.7

Since Python 3.7, calling Py_Initialize() twice triggers a fatal error.

Simply remove the Py_Initialize() call from PyInit__jpype(), since it is just useless.

author: Martin
message:
Add testcases for mutlithreading proxy execution.

Java will call registered proxies (callbacks) in a multithreaded
environment using the ExecutorService. Jpype will throw an exception or
exit with an access violation.

author: Jeremy Morse
message:
Support conversion of Class objects to java

Passing objects into java goes via JPClass::convertToJava, which
transforms source objects into java handles. However, conversion _from_
java class objects isn't currently implemented, and thus any class
argument gets erroneously transformed to null.

author: justussc
message:
fix calls from python to methods taking integer/long primitives for larger integers
   * overload resolution with JLong wrapper did not work (was checking for _int instead of _long)
   * on 64bit linux systems LONG_MAX is 2^63-1 and therefore returning JPyInt::asLong as a jint cuts of higher bits for values >= 2**31 or < -2**31
   * similar problem as above for all py3 on all systems as we have no long type anymore but only int
   * if a python exception was set we need to throw a PythonException not a JPypeException otherwise the message is overwritten
   * ref to member of temporary fixed in jpype_javaarray
   * tp_init has to either return 0 or -1

author: Martin K. Scherer
message:
Merge pull request #54 from marscher/primitive_setter_improvment

Primitive array setter improvement, which avoids conversion of every element to a HostRef wrapper.

Error checking is performed in the actual implementation of the setRange function in primitive type classes via Python C-API - this is optimistic, but avoids an additional function call pair for every element (canConvertToJava and convertToJava). So memory is allocated/freed even when we conversion will fail. But considering large arrays this is really important.
